
With the files in this directory the datapointtypes and datapoints can be
generated for the whole PVSS database.
There are three types of files:
 - the base files contain the database structure that has to be generated.
 - the list files contain the values a variable can have.
 - the dpdef files define in human-readable format the complex datapointtypes.

The syntax of the lines of the dpdef files is:
[<structure>.]<parametername>		<parametertype>

With parametertype:

paramtype		PVSS datapoint type
-----------------------------------
string			DPEL_STRING
bool			DPEL_BOOL
uint			DPEL_UINT
int				DPEL_INT
float			DPEL_FLOAT
double			DPEL_FLOAT
stringArr		DPEL_DYN_STRING
boolArr			DPEL_DYN_BOOL
uintArr			DPEL_DYN_UINT
intArr			DPEL_DYN_INT
floatArr		DPEL_DYN_FLOAT
doubleArr		DPEL_DYN_FLOAT


The create_db_files script generates two types of files:

create_db_files PVSS	creates a file with datapointtypes and a file with
						the PVSSdatapoints.
create_db_files C++		creates a c++ headerfile with constants that can be 
						used in c++ programs to access the datapoints.

